YCzvRxgDzuYXa","target":"recwFUncFiNWPsPWN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec8YCzvRxgDzuYXa","target":"rectrAkGtrZH5LMp8","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec8YCzvRxgDzuYXa","target":"recIJFRcqI6KbKgXb","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec8YCzvRxgDzuYXa","target":"recYRlZ4ewWJACJQ6","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec6MsoXea0puCDWi","ref":"2Chr.30.1","text":"And Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah, and wrote letters also to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the house of the LORD at Jerusalem, to keep the passover unto the LORD God of Israel.","year":-726},{"id":"recBah7QLfYuGtUSc","ref":"2Chr.30.2","text":"For the king had taken counsel, and his princes, and all the congregation in Jerusalem, to keep the passover in the second month.","year":-726},{"id":"recCnwz9OnQXBqOvh","ref":"2Chr.30.3","text":"For they could not keep it at that time, because the priests had not sanctified themselves sufficiently, neither had the people gathered themselves together to Jerusalem.","year":-726},{"id":"rec77lEtjmxMACCeR","ref":"2Chr.30.4","text":"And the thing pleased the king and all the congregation.","year":-726},{"id":"recVNdLEFtmp1zdDP","ref":"2Chr.30.5","text":"So they established a decree to make proclamation throughout all Israel, from Beersheba even to Dan, that they should come to keep the passover unto the LORD God of Israel at Jerusalem: for they had not done it of a long time in such sort as it was written.","year":-726},{"id":"recj0zMMQEdDlu9Cp","ref":"2Chr.30.6","text":"So the posts went with the letters from the king and his princes throughout all Israel and Judah, and according to the commandment of the king, saying, Ye children of Israel, turn again unto the LORD God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, and he will return to the remnant of you, that are escaped out of the hand of the kings of Assyria.","year":-726},{"id":"reci28zRwEzJhDZ32","ref":"2Chr.30.7","text":"And be not ye like your fathers, and like your brethren, which trespassed against the LORD God of their fathers, who therefore gave them up to desolation, as ye see.","year":-726},{"id":"recN7j6lxBCU1Yy6Y","ref":"2Chr.30.8","text":"Now be ye not stiffnecked, as your fathers were, but yield yourselves unto the LORD, and enter into his sanctuary, which he hath sanctified for ever: and serve the LORD your God, that the fierceness of his wrath may turn away from you.","year":-726}]}
